  "returns": "The inputwindow_lengthis a positive integer controlling the\nreturned window size.periodicflag determines whether the returned\nwindow trims off the last duplicate value from the symmetric window and is\nready to be used as a periodic window with functions liketorch.stft(). Therefore, ifperiodicis true, theNNNin\nabove formula is in factwindow_length+1\\text{window\\_length} + 1window_length+1. Also, we always havetorch.blackman_window(L,periodic=True)equal totorch.blackman_window(L+1,periodic=False)[:-1].",
